The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for image analysis, specifically for detecting primary particles in agglomerated and partially sintered particles. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks for training the model also suggests that it falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with image processing and analysis, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method in comparison to other automated image-based particle size analysis methods, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
